  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">BEE HIVES FOR RURAL FARMERS TO EDUCATE THEIR KIDS</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Unpredictable rain seasons, longer droughts, crop diseases and inadequate crop pollinators have greatly affected the income of rural farmers in Kikandwa villages due to poor crop yields. Majority have resorted to charcoal burning thus massive tree cutting. KIRUCODO is considering beekeeping profitable, environment friendly and less-time demanding if local farmers are supported with basic materials. 50 farmers will be reached at in 6 months with 5 hives each enough to support 3 kids in school.</narrative>
  </description>
